AapicPhonotactics

ProtoAapicChernobyl

## Sentence Structure

Sentences are exclusively (S)ubject (O)bject (V)erb. In addition, noun phrases (NP) exclusively come in animacy order. Therefore, the verb must change form to accommodate word order while conveying the intended meaning.

Examples:

* I gave my mother an egg.
* 1HU-IN.POSS mother 1HU one egg REV-give
* a-ti bba a iti igga toak-otooki
* My mother was given one egg by me.

* Don't shoot the messenger.
* 2HU messenger shoot-PROH
* i patokippah okiptiigi-ib

* I see and hear you. (typical semiformal greeting)
* 1HU 2HU see hear
* a i apiitah aabih
* 2MO 1HU REV-see REV-hear (when greeting a mother)
* ii a toak-apiitah toak-aabih

* I have seen many wedding feasts. (implying age)
* 1HU many wedding_feast see-PERF
* a gitakta itdakpokkodi apiitah-ipk

* I am at your service.
* 1HU 2HU AL.POSS helper remain.
* a i togh gitta biik
* 2MO AL.POSS helper 1HU remain. (when addressing a mother)
* ii togh gitta a biik

* An animal bites my father's arm.
* 1HU-IN.POSS father-IN.POSS arm animal REV-bite
* a-ti daptippakh-ti gitta tokkig toak-daaki

* The coconut hits the warrior in the face.
* fighter 3HU-IN.POSS face large nut LOC-INST-hit-PASS
* patkakkit o-ti apitabbik pokodi obottik bik-togh-khaatka-ogh

* I see myself in the water.
* 1HU water REF-LOC-see
* a pittoh ik-bik-apiitah

---

### Grammar workshop

#### Goblin stepping

* I try to get him to step on the goblin.
* 1HU 3HU scrawny-monster AD-walk-IRR aim
* a o ik-opoptokki otko-dioota-khai hapoota
* I attempt that he may walk on the scrawny monster.

* I try to cause him to step on the goblin.
* 1HU try 3IN-AL.POSS 1HU 3HU scrawny-monster CAU-AD-walk-IRR
* a hapoota tibik a o ik-opoptokki da-otko-dioota-khai
* I attempt therefore I may cause that he walk on the scrawny monster.

* I try to force/trick/persuade him to step on the goblin.
* 1HU 3HU force/trick/persuade-PASS try 3IN-AL.POSS 3HU scrawny-monster AD-walk-IRR
* a o FORCE/TRICK/PERSUADE-ogh hapoota tibik o ik-opoptokki otko-dioota-khai
* I attempt he is forced/tricked/persuaded therefore he may walk on the scrawny monster 

* I beg/dare him to step on the goblin.

* I insist/demand that he step on the goblin.

* My goal is that he steps on the goblin.
* 1HU-IN.POSS goal 3HU scrawny-monster AD-walk-IRR be_same
* a-ti hapotta o ik-opoptokki otko-dioota-khai iiki

* Hopefully I am making him step on the goblin.
* 
* I hope because I may cause that he walk on the scrawny monster.

#### Other sentences

* Oje carved the arrow’s fine point.

* They are to finish boiling the well water. Then, they will cook with or drink it.

* Your manner of feeding pigeons irritates me.

* I washed John’s feet, they looked dirty.

* He didn’t hear clearly what he said, and so didn’t know this secret word.

