gitati | 6-8 | "hand two"
itgita | 8-14 | "two hand"
gitakta | 12+ / lots | "hand hand"
|/table

---

## Derivational Morphology

|table
morph | meaning | source
- | - | -
ak- | tool | "do"
akta- | collection | "many"
da- | causative | "reason"
ik- | diminutive | "small"
pat- | person who | "write"
pok- | augmentative | "enlarge"
pipti- | adjective | "similarity"
|/table

The ik- diminutive has a negative connotation. Think shriveled or scrawny.

The pok- augmentative has a positive connotation. Think well-fed or chubby.

The adjectival prefix is typically only added to a stem when it is of higher animacy than the lexical noun.

---

## Verb Markers

### Prefixes (applicative moods)

|table
mark | etymology | verb form | gloss
- | - | -
ak- | a:ka | agentive AG | by
bik- | b:ik | locative LOC | at
bo- | bo:ki | inessive IN | within
da- | d:ap | causative CAUS | causes
gi- | gi:ta | objective OBJ | addtl. patient
ik- | i:ki | reflexive REF | -self
kot- | kot:oki | benefactive BEN | for
oki- | oki:pih | adelative ADEL | from
otko- | ot:oko | adessive ADES | on
pi- | pipi:ti | comitative COM | along with
toak- | to:gih a:ka | reversive REV | swaps S with DO
togh- | to:gih | instrumental INST | by means of
|/table

### Suffixes (other moods and aspects)

|table
mark | etymology | verb form | gloss
- | - | -
-ap | d:ap | imperative IMP | do
-ib | ib:oh | prohibitive PROH | do not
-ipk | b:ik | perfect PERF | completed or past action
-ikha | khi:ka | negative NEG | does not
-khai | ikh:ai | irrealis IRR | perhaps
-pta | pa:ta | double passive 2PASS | takes no S or DO; old IO is new S
-tikh | t:ikh | triple passive 3PASS | takes no S, DO, or IO
-ogh | to:gih | passive PASS | takes no S; old DO is new S
|/table

The double and triple passive indicate the verb takes two or three less arguments respectively.






